%% ODH Dashboard - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAuth as Kubernetes API<br/>TokenReview/SAR
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard Backend<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant FedModule as Federated Module<br/>(e.g., model-registry-ui)<br/>8043/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PlatformSvc as Platform Service<br/>(e.g., Pipelines)<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Browser,PlatformSvc: Flow 1: User Accessing Dashboard UI

    Browser->>Gateway: GET / (HTTPS/443)<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward (HTTPS/8443)<br/>TLS passthrough
    RBAC->>K8sAuth: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>(can user list projects?)
    K8sAuth-->>RBAC: Auth result
    RBAC->>Dashboard: Forward (HTTP/8080 localhost)<br/>X-Auth-Request-User/Groups headers
    Dashboard-->>RBAC: HTML/JS/CSS (React SPA)
    RBAC-->>Gateway: Response (HTTPS)
    Gateway-->>Browser: Dashboard UI

    Note over Browser,PlatformSvc: Flow 2: Managing K8s Resources (e.g., Notebooks)

    Browser->>Gateway: POST /api/k8s/... (HTTPS/443)<br/>Bearer Token
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward (HTTPS/8443)
    RBAC->>K8sAuth: Validate user token
    K8sAuth-->>RBAC: Authorized
    RBAC->>Dashboard: Forward with user identity
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: K8s API call (HTTPS/443)<br/>User Bearer token (forwarded)
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Resource response
    Dashboard-->>Browser: JSON response

    Note over Browser,PlatformSvc: Flow 3: Federated Module Loading

    Browser->>RBAC: GET /model-registry/* (HTTPS/8443)<br/>Bearer Token
    RBAC->>K8sAuth: Validate user
    K8sAuth-->>RBAC: Authorized
    Browser->>FedModule: Load federated bundle (HTTPS/8043)<br/>X-Forwarded-Access-Token header
    FedModule->>K8sAPI: K8s API call (HTTPS/443)<br/>Forwarded user token
    K8sAPI-->>FedModule: Resource data
    FedModule-->>Browser: Federated UI components

    Note over Browser,PlatformSvc: Flow 4: Proxying to Platform Services

    Browser->>Gateway: POST /api/service/pipelines/* (HTTPS/443)<br/>Bearer Token
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward (HTTPS/8443)
    RBAC->>Dashboard: Authenticated request
    Dashboard->>PlatformSvc: Proxy request (HTTPS/8443)<br/>Forwarded user token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    PlatformSvc-->>Dashboard: Service response
    Dashboard-->>Browser: Proxied response
